Reminder to everyone!! Potluck time!!

Next Tuesday (July 30th) is the last cheese club meeting of the term! üßÄüßÄ

We‚Äôre bringing back as many of your winning cheeses as we can, but we are also having a potluck!

Cheeses will operate as normal ($4 for walk-ins, no fee for members) but you need to BRING something to GET something for the potluck! 

Don‚Äôt feel pressured to bring much‚Äî we‚Äôre going for variety not quantity. Just bring something that at least 5 people can try. (eg: bag of chips, baked goods, candies, chocolate bar, meatballs, more cheese- ahem.) 

As the interim president, I feel obliged to share my potluck picks with everyone. I may have went overboard but you are all worth it ü§ó See my haul on the next slide üëÄ I‚Äôm also bringing a secret cheesy item so I hope you all come ü§≠

DM us or email ccch.uw@gmail.com if you have any questions!

Bring a takeout container too if you can üòâ

caption: It‚Äôs was incredible for our team to qualify and compete in FSGP for the first time in 5 years! It was a long journey for us 2.5 years ago when we started this project from nothing and we couldn‚Äôt have been more proud of everyone that helped us build this solar car! Although we were not able to qualify for ASC, we‚Äôre still happy with what we were able to achieve over the duration of Scrutineering and FSGP with 100km on the track and a fastest lap of 5:55. We learned a lot during competition and from talking to other teams so we‚Äôll be back with many ideas and improvements for our next car, MSXVI! As we look towards MSXVI, we‚Äôre looking for eager new members to help us in this new chapter of the team. Looking forward to seeing everyone in the Fall Term for recruitment!!
accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Midnight Sun Solar Car Team on July 29, 2024 tagging @uwengsoc, and @uwaterlooeng. May be an image of racing vehicles, race car and text.

caption: Day 7: The final day of FSGP is here! After two days on track MSXV drove a total of 20 laps (62 miles) with a fastest lap time of 5:55! Joining 24 other teams on the track, we also had the pleasure of interviewing with ABC WBKO news on solar cars. Various mechanical and electrical issues kept us off the track for a good portion of the day but the team pulled through to drive 14 laps on day 3. As we pack up and head to display day, we thank NCM Motorsports park for being our home for the past 7 days!
accessibility_caption: Photo by Midnight Sun Solar Car Team on July 25, 2024. May be an image of 3 people, people racing vehicles, race car and text.

caption: Day 6: WE ARE ON THE TRACK! Despite some rough weather hitting the racetrack and significantly impacting most of the teams, MSXV raced it‚Äôs first 3.1 miles today with Michael behind the wheel and the team has never been more excited to see it drive! Our time on track was limited, but MSXV finished the day with 6 laps completed and officially puts us on the scoreboard. Check out the video of our first lap!
accessibility_caption: Photo by Midnight Sun Solar Car Team on July 25, 2024. May be an image of racing vehicles, race car and text.

caption: Day 5: FSGP Race day is here! We gathered with the rest of the attending teams for a sunny team photo before getting right back to the pits for some last minute changes to push through dynamics. Michael was the first driver to be fully cleared to race, and our other two drivers cleared driver ops and are working to join the other teams out on the track!
accessibility_caption: Photo by Midnight Sun Solar Car Team on July 25, 2024. May be an image of racing vehicles, race car and text.
